When editing a pull request, we have the following error : "An unexpected error occurred". The ajax request to {{https://bitbucket.org/!api/1.0/repositories/ccmbenchmark/ccmcms_linternaute/pullrequests/tasks/d9215818-3521-4692-99fc-634dbb4767b7?_=1450173236167}} has a 500 HTTP status with the following content :

{code}
#!json

{"error": {"message": "[Errno 2] No such file or directory", "id": "8c52b9856f1c40c8995ee7624addeb18"}}
{code}

Actually all "Pull-Request POST" services seems broken, it seems to be related to this issue.

Since the recent DNS update, some of our api calls are failing, but only the calls via OAUTH that use the api endpoint {{https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0}}

{{https://bitbucket.org/api/2.0}} actually works just fine.

It doesn&#x27;t seem to be directly DNS related, as far as I can tell, since our other calls are working fine (it must be able to resolve bitbucket still...) and the api.bitbucket route does work if we use basic authentication...

{code}
curl  --data &#x27;{...}&#x27; https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/<owner>/<repo_slug>/hooks
{code}

results in something like this:

{code}
{"uuid": "{ec96bf6b-abb2-4f30-90b9-0178342c9fc5}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/<owner>/<repo_slug>/hooks/%7Bec96bf6b-abb2-4f30-90b9-0178342c9fc5%7D"}}, ...
{code}

I&#x27;m trying to use the API to create an issue and I get the following response:

{code}
<ul class="errorlist"><li>title<ul class="errorlist"><li>This field is required.</li></ul></li></ul>
{code}

even though I&#x27;m sending the title parameter (and the content btw). I&#x27;m using the exact same method that I&#x27;m using for other endpoints that are working.

I&#x27;m using this library https://github.com/codacy/bitbucket-scala-client, and the method is here https://github.com/codacy/bitbucket-scala-client/blob/master/src/main/scala/com/codacy/client/bitbucket/service/IssueServices.scala

This library is using OAuth 1, if it&#x27;s important.

To reproduce it:

* clone the repo
* {{sbt console}}
* {{import com.codacy.client.bitbucket.client.BitbucketClient}}
* {{val client = new BitbucketClient("key","secretKey","token","secretToken")}}
* {{import com.codacy.client.bitbucket.service._}}
* {{val service = new IssueServices(client)}}
* {{service.createIssue("pedrorijo91", "ttttt", "TITLE", "BODY")}}

and response:

{code}
res2: com.codacy.client.bitbucket.client.RequestResponse[com.codacy.client.bitbucket.Issue] = RequestResponse(None,BAD REQUEST,true)
{code}

Hi,\\
when creating a new Mercurial repository in the BitBucket web interface and then trying to clone it with SourceTree v1.6.23.0 using the "Clone in SourceTree" button from the Repository Setup page, I get following error

{code}
#!bash

  hg clone -b default https://maiple-telerobotics@bitbucket.org/maiple-telerobotics/initrepo C:\Projects\initrepo
  abort: unknown branch &#x27;default&#x27;!

  Completed with errors, see above.
{code}

At the same time trying to create a branch through the web interface will fail because it would require an existing branch.\\
It seems that the repository is not initialized correctly on creation if that is done from the web interface.
